MtSigCommSingle            package:sigcomm             R Documentation

_C_o_m_p_u_t_e _s_t_a_t_i_s_t_i_c_a_l _s_i_g_n_i_f_i_c_a_n_c_e _o_f _a _s_i_n_g_l_e _c_o_m_m_u_n_i_t_y.

_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     Compute statistical significance of a single community.

_U_s_a_g_e:

     MtSigCommSingle(group_s, G, adjG, edges, d, N, m, version = 3,
       borderp = 0.25, nmcsims = 100, return_mean = FALSE)
     
_A_r_g_u_m_e_n_t_s:

 group_s: (integer) The community.

       G: (igraph) The network in igraph format.

    adjG: (dgCMatrix) The adjacency matrix of the network.

   edges: (integer matrix) The edgelist of the network.

       d: (integer) The degree vector of the network.

       N: (integer) The number of nodes in the network.

       m: (integer) Twice the number of edges in the network.

 version: (integer, default: 3) Version of the method to use.

 borderp: (double, default: 0.25) Proportion of community to use as the
          border.

 nmcsims: (integer, default: 100) Number of monte carlo simulations of
          p-values to produce.

return_mean: (bool, default: FALSE) Whether to return mean or median of
          mc p-values.


